{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_14","type":"reasoning","text":"**Inspecting load issues**\n\nI need to check the load_home_data function because it might be loading too many images every refresh, potentially duplicating all rows with large images and causing memory issues. This could be because a fallback image is being decoded each time from disk, and previous models might not be dropping. I suspect something in the auto-refresh loop between lines 380-500 could be leaking or causing duplication, so I'll inspect that area closely."}}
