{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_34","type":"reasoning","text":"**Examining memory issues**\n\nI'm exploring a potential memory leak related to blurred backgrounds in animations. It's interesting—there might not be any data loaded without users. Still, could there be a huge amount of text? I doubt it. I wonder if the VmRSS is high due to file cache or issues with font loading. There's a warning in the logs about memory usage approaching 2.5GB, but that doesn't seem to match the actual condition. I need to check the current code for timeouts on resource loading, as many loads could be running indefinitely.\n**Investigating potential fixes**\n\nI’m considering adding a timeout around the functions `load_public_users` and `load_home_data`; maybe that’ll address the issues noted in the spec and logs. Even though the network error is returned quickly, I wonder if the memory crash results from repeated unresolved calls. There's a chance there's an obvious memory leak related to the user avatar’s fallback text. I think it uses the full user name instead of just the first character. I should check the git history for recent commits that might mention out-of-memory issues related to video thumbnails."}}
